I’m the only programmer for my team and I’m trying to improve our autonomous code, I found pathplanner and it looks like it would be very useful, we are using a kitbot which means we have differential drive, we added a ground intake because we are going to worlds, however I have zero clue how to include these paths into our code, I imported the pathplanner library and I think it may be a lot harder to use this because we are using differential drive and not swerve. I’m not using command-based I’m using timed robot, could someone help me?

Hi! We also have a tank drive, and for pathplanner we use configureRamsete() from AutoBuilder (Build an Auto | PathPlanner Docs).
The only thing that changes from PathWeaver is that, and that you must use the following lines of code to get and pass the chassisSpeeds:
public void autoDrive(ChassisSpeeds tankChassisSpeeds)
{
DifferentialDriveWheelSpeeds tankWheelsSpeeds = tankKinematics.toWheelSpeeds(tankChassisSpeeds);
tankWheelsSpeeds.desaturate(0.75);

differentialDrive.tankDrive(-tankWheelsSpeeds.leftMetersPerSecond, -tankWheelsSpeeds.rightMetersPerSecond);

}
public ChassisSpeeds getSpeeds()
{
return m_kinematics.toChassisSpeeds(getWheelSpeed());
}
